      <byline class="print_byline">By RICHARD PERRY</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A group of local witches gathered late last month in La Plaza Cultural, a small garden at Ninth Street and Avenue C, to mark a relatively rare lunar event: the second full moon in the same month, sometimes known as a blue moon. The celebration featured readings and meditation as the witches formed a circle around candles.</p>
      </block>
